Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho has picked little-known William Kingi as his running mate.Director of communication Richard Chacha confirmed the appointment, saying Joho will officially unveil Kingi tomorrow. Many thought Joho would pick either county secretary Francis Thoya or Education executive Lewa Tendai, both from the Mijikenda community.Joho had to look for a new running mate after Hazel Katana defected to Jubilee. Kingi heads the School of Business and is a lecturer at the Mombasa Technical University. He is also the head of the Secretariat of the Jumuiya ya Kaunti za Pwani.He is a PhD holder from Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology. On Monday, Senator Hassan Omar picked Linda Shuma, 39, a businesswoman, as his running mate.